Builders FirstSource is a supplier of manufactured components and materials to home builders. Its products include doors and mill work, trusses, wall panels and stairs, and kitchen and bath components. The company has field offices located in nine states in… MoreBuilders FirstSource is a supplier of manufactured components and materials to home builders. Its products include doors and mill work, trusses, wall panels and stairs, and kitchen and bath components. The company has field offices located in nine states in the Southeastern part of the United States.

Builders FirstSource completed an acquisition of ProBuild Holdings LLC in July, 2015.
The Vice President and Chief Information Officer oversees all information technology operations and initiatives at at Builders FirstSource. The responsibilities of the information technology department are divided among a group of managers who oversee specific areas of IT, including telecommunications, training information systems, software and systems, and information systems. The… MoreThe Vice President and Chief Information Officer oversees all information technology operations and initiatives at at Builders FirstSource. The responsibilities of the information technology department are divided among a group of managers who oversee specific areas of IT, including telecommunications, training information systems, software and systems, and information systems. The Manager of HRIS manages a group of technology professionals accountable for the HR departments' business systems.

Builders FirstSource's data center is located at the company's headquarters in Dallas, TX and holds about 45 Windows servers based on VMware virtual server machines. The company has over 35 additional servers located throughout the United States in its field offices. Builders FirstSource has a long standing partnership with Ultrabac Software to provide its disaster recovery solutions. The data center and field officers are all equipped with a special data drive which images the servers daily. Storage that is older than two days is stored at an off-site location.





