 Continental Building Products Inc has a higher fundamental rating then Builders FirstSource Inc which has an impact on the head-to-head comparison. The CML Star Rating is an objective, quantifiable measure of a company's operating and financial condition. 
		The rating is computed by measuring numerous elements of the company's current financial data and their associated changes over time.
		
		Now, let's dive into the two companies to compare them.






➤ Income Statement
First we turn to the income statement and compare revenue, earnings and revenue per employee for both companies. We note that simple revenue comparisons 
								do not impact the rating.
								
↪ Builders FirstSource Inc has substantially higher revenue in the last year than Continental Building Products Inc. 
						Raw revenue comps do not affect the head to head rating.Revenue↪  Both BLDR and CBPX show positive earnings over the last year with the edge to BLDR.Net Income↪ CBPX generates massively larger revenue per employee ($772,000) than BLDR ($255,000).Revenue per Employee
			 ($ Millions)




➤ Margins
Next we create some derived metrics to compare the the amount of revenue earned per dollar of expense and the amount of free cash flow earned per dollar of revenue. Margins are one of the fairest ways to compare companies since they remove some of the bias of large versus small numbers.
								
↪ Continental Building Products Inc generates $1.19 in revenue for every $1 of expense, notably higher than Builders FirstSource Inc's $1.05.Revenue per Dollar of Expense↪ CBPX generates $0.26 in levered free cash flow for every $1 of revenue, 
					while BLDR generates a cash flow loss of $-0.00  per $1 of revenue.Free Cash Flow
		per Dollar of Revenue




➤ Growth
Finally we compare the financial metrics related to growth: revenue growth rates and price to sales.
								
↪ Both companies are growing revenue. Builders FirstSource Inc is growing revenue massively faster than Continental Building Products Inc.Revenue Growth↪  For every $1 in revenue, the stock market prices in $0.22 in market cap for BLDR and $2.08 in market cap for CBPX.Price to Sales



